Anyway, we did our best to look out for his son, give him stuff, etc.  Then, one day Sadiel found his son crying in front of the computer.  Two guys in Gfay had scammed him out of some equipment, got him killed, and mercilessly made fun of him.  His son quit and Sadiel followed soon thereafter.<br>
<br>
People who do that crap are the lowest form of life.  Think about the real person behind the toon or message board username before you take out your pathetic RL frustrations on him/her.  He/she may just be a kid trying to having fun or a person with serious RL problems.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF8DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/umytzle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mytzle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif></span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#006400>(9/4/01 9:27:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=722.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /Salute. </span><hr size=1> Hrmmm, this may be slightly offtopic, but posts like the one I just read about loser players is the reason my son will not be playing Everquest. He's 8 years old, and cool as hell (he gets that from me not his mother :P) and I will keep him from as many assholes as I can. EQ is full fo them. What bothers me most is I cannot get my hands on them. If someone fucks with my son they better be ready to deal with me. So in order to save myself needless stress and more importantly let my son learn that life is cruel and harsh after he enjoys a full childhood, I keep him from this game. It is fun, but children are not equipped to deal with the sheer vileness that is personified in many EQ players. <br>
<br>
Which brings me to another point... I find it amusing that people sit here and flame back and forth, it is one of the things that has kept me on usenet since before most fo you knew what the internet was. But there comes a point where I have to wonder about motivation. I mean where does this come from? My theory is that most of the 'loser flamers', and I will not name names, are both physically and mentally unable to be effective in society. usually these people in my experience are very under sized, usually slow on the uptake and such. A battle of wits is no fun unless you have a sword, and these people don't even have a swiss-army knife. I ocne felt sorry for them, but people should be able to control their anger. I now simply view them with apathy, and occaisionally as a form of amusement. <br>
<br>
The you have the other type of flamer, the well spoken, extremely funny, razor tongued devil. Perhaps this person doesn't annoy me so much because they actually think about what they want to say, say something worth saying (as far as flaming goes) and are creative. An 'alpha flamer' if you will. I have found these people tend to scoff at society and many others in general. This is ok by me, I think our society is a cesspool. Which brings me to my final point...<br>
<br>
Unt, I feel your pain man. These boards and any online community will resemble society, I can only hope that someday we can cull the herd, or maybe Darwins law will kick in full force. I'm sorry the pathetic ravings of morons drove you to this decision, but perhaps you will come to find some sort of peace without this place. That is all we can hope for anyways, peace and contentment <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
